---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/page/PageHero.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About | Virtual Ventures"
  description="Learn about Virtual Ventures, a UK-based handmade workshop for crochet creatures, original patterns, laser engraved details, 3D printed craft helpers, planners, books and creative experiments."
  showFooterBreadcrumbs={false}
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="About"
    title="About Virtual Ventures"
    description="A UK-based handmade workshop for crochet creatures, pattern ideas, laser engraved details, 3D printed helpers, planners, tutorials and useful little creative things."
  />

  <main class="page-shell about-page">
    <section id="hello-from-the-workshop" class="about-intro">
      <p class="eyebrow">
        <span aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
        Hello from the workshop
        <span aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
      </p>

      <h1>Handmade things, useful ideas and a little everyday magic.</h1>

      <p>
        Virtual Ventures is a UK-based creative workshop for crochet creatures,
        custom patterns, engraved items, planners, books, tutorials, 3D printed
        helpers and the odd useful little thing that starts life as a scribble
        in a notebook.
      </p>

      <p>
        This space is being built slowly and honestly. Right now, that means
        designing the website, shaping the shop, planning future patterns,
        testing ideas and documenting the process as it grows. The aim is
        simple: share creativity, keep making, and hopefully send a few smiles
        out into the world along the way.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section
      id="maker-behind-virtual-ventures"
      class="about-story-section about-story-left"
    >
      <div class="about-story-content">
        <p class="eyebrow">
          <span aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
          Who am I?
        </p>

        <h2>The maker behind Virtual Ventures</h2>

        <p>
          I’m the maker behind Virtual Ventures. I’m happiest when my hands are
          busy and an idea has somewhere to go. Crochet is the heart of the
          workshop, but my busy maker-brain does not politely stay in one box,
          so the workshop also includes laser engraving, 3D printing, website
          building, planners, books, tutorials and whatever creative rabbit hole
          starts glowing next.
        </p>

        <p>
          For privacy and safety, I keep personal details separate from the
          business. Virtual Ventures is the public face of the work: the making,
          the learning, the experiments, the finished pieces and the stories
          behind them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      id="why-virtual-ventures"
      class="about-story-section about-story-right"
    >
      <div class="about-story-content">
        <p class="eyebrow">
          <span aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
          Why Virtual Ventures?
        </p>

        <h2>Because creativity is better when it gets shared.</h2>

        <p>
          Virtual Ventures exists because I needed a place to share my
          creativity with the world. Over time, people have fallen in love with
          crochet pieces I made, especially while following other makers’
          patterns, and that has meant more than I can properly explain.
        </p>

        <p>
          Now it feels like time to start creating my own patterns, sharing what
          I learn, and building something that can grow into a proper handmade
          business. Not just the shiny finished bits either. I want to share the
          successes, the failures, the “why is this stitch count being
          dramatic?” moments, and the occasional “whoops, looks like I broke the
          3D printer” chapter too.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="what-do-i-make" class="about-story-section about-story-left">
      <div class="about-story-content">
        <p class="eyebrow">
          <span aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
          What do I make?
        </p>

        <h2>Crochet, engraving, planners, tools and tiny useful things.</h2>

        <p>
          Virtual Ventures will bring together handmade crochet items, custom
          crochet patterns, engraved pieces, planners, books, YouTube tutorials
          and eventually STL files for 3D printed craft helpers.
        </p>

        <p>
          Some products will be physical, some will be digital, and some will
          begin as experiments before they earn a proper place on the shelf. The
          common thread is that everything should feel thoughtful, useful,
          handmade or genuinely helpful. Cute is lovely. Useful cute is even
          better.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      id="handmade-honesty"
      class="about-story-section about-story-right"
    >
      <div class="about-story-content">
        <p class="eyebrow">
          <span aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
          Handmade honesty
        </p>

        <h2>Patterns take time, testing and real hands.</h2>

        <p>
          AI is useful, but it is not the maker here. I use AI to help turn
          rambling notes into clearer wording, check spelling, organise ideas
          and verify code. If it is ever used in another way, I will be honest
          about it.
        </p>

        <p>
          The designs, crochet work, photos, editing and finished products are
          created by me. Future patterns will be made, tested, checked and
          improved by real hands, not generated and tossed online like a yarn
          ball into a ceiling fan.
        </p>

        <p>
          The flood of AI crochet patterns online is worrying because crochet
          patterns need more than confident-looking instructions. They need
          testing. They need fixing. They need someone to actually make the
          thing. Virtual Ventures is a safe, honest space for handmade work,
          real process and eventually ideas shaped with the community too.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      id="behind-the-scenes"
      class="about-story-section about-story-left"
    >
      <div class="about-story-content">
        <p class="eyebrow">
          <span aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
          Behind the scenes
        </p>

        <h2>The good bits, the messy bits and the learning bits.</h2>

        <p>
          A lot of business pages only show the polished final product. Virtual
          Ventures will show more than that. The blog is here for the making
          process, the experiments, the lessons, the broken attempts, the
          improvements and the tiny victories that happen before something is
          ready to sell.
        </p>

        <p>
          That might mean a crochet idea that needs three versions before it
          works, a website feature that takes longer than planned, a laser test
          that teaches me what not to do, or a 3D print that fails spectacularly
          but still earns its place in the story.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      id="dog-friendly-workshop"
      class="about-story-section about-story-right about-story-photo-stack"
    >
      <div class="about-story-content">
        <p class="eyebrow">
          <span aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
          Dog-friendly workshop
        </p>

        <h2>A tiny note about dog glitter.</h2>

        <p>
          Virtual Ventures is made in a real home workshop, which means dogs may
          occasionally appear in behind-the-scenes photos. Finished items will
          always be handled carefully, but if physical crochet pieces are sold
          in the future, I’ll be clear and honest that they are made in a
          dog-friendly space.
        </p>

        <picture class="about-inline-image">
          <source
            srcset="/images/about/about-dog-friendly.webp"
            type="image/webp"
          />

          <img
            src="/images/about/about-dog-friendly.jpg"
            alt="A crochet blanket in progress with yarn, colour notes and two dogs resting nearby in a cosy dog-friendly home workshop."
            loading="lazy"
            decoding="async"
          />
        </picture>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="what-comes-next" class="about-story-section about-story-left">
      <div class="about-story-content">
        <p class="eyebrow">
          <span aria-hidden="true">✦</span>
          What comes next?
        </p>

        <h2>Patterns, tutorials, live streams and a growing handmade shop.</h2>

        <p>
          Virtual Ventures is still growing. The next steps include building the
          shop, creating original crochet patterns, making YouTube tutorials,
          preparing planners and books, designing engraved items, testing 3D
          printed helpers and eventually running cosy live streams.
        </p>

        <p>
          This is not trying to become a giant polished factory. It is a
          handmade corner with a lot of ideas, a lot of learning, and a
          community-shaped future. I want Virtual Ventures to become a place
          where people can follow the process, trust the products and feel part
          of the adventure.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about-closing-note" class="about-closing-card">
      <p>
        Virtual Ventures exists to share creativity, document the process and
        make handmade things that carry a little smile with them.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
